Despite of the political, historical and geographical factors influencing the boundaries of countries and states, human populations have always flocked together into settlements41. As such, our proposed GHPM model starts from a targeted, real-world geographical area A (e.g., a continent, a country, a state), quantified by a set S of (real) settlements, which represent the basis of human organization and cooperation. In contrast to the abstract representation of network communities, each settlement \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
